{
  "book": 18,
  "chapter": 9,
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Then Job spoke again: "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“Yes, I know all this is true in principle. But how can a person be declared innocent in God’s sight? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Yes, I know all this is true in principle. But how can a person be declared innocent in God’s sight?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "If someone wanted to take God to court, would it be possible to answer him even once in a thousand times? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "If someone wanted to take God to court, would it be possible to answer him even once in a thousand times?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For God is so wise and so mighty. Who has ever challenged him successfully? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For God is so wise and so mighty. Who has ever challenged him successfully?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“Without warning, he moves the mountains, overturning them in his anger. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Without warning, he moves the mountains, overturning them in his anger."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "He shakes the earth from its place, and its foundations tremble. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He shakes the earth from its place, and its foundations tremble."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "If he commands it, the sun won’t rise and the stars won’t shine. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "If he commands it, the sun won’t rise and the stars won’t shine."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "He alone has spread out the heavens and marches on the waves of the sea. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He alone has spread out the heavens and marches on the waves of the sea."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "He made all the stars—the Bear and Orion, the Pleiades and the constellations of the southern sky. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He made all the stars—the Bear and Orion, the Pleiades and the constellations of the southern sky."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "He does great things too marvelous to understand. He performs countless miracles. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He does great things too marvelous to understand. He performs countless miracles."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“Yet when he comes near, I cannot see him. When he moves by, I do not see him go. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Yet when he comes near, I cannot see him. When he moves by, I do not see him go."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "If he snatches someone in death, who can stop him? Who dares to ask, ‘What are you doing?’ "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "If he snatches someone in death, who can stop him? Who dares to ask, ‘What are you doing?’"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "And God does not restrain his anger. Even the monsters of the sea are crushed beneath his feet. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "And God does not restrain his anger. Even the monsters of the sea are crushed beneath his feet."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“So who am I, that I should try to answer God or even reason with him? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“So who am I, that I should try to answer God or even reason with him?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Even if I were right, I would have no defense. I could only plead for mercy. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Even if I were right, I would have no defense. I could only plead for mercy."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "And even if I summoned him and he responded, I’m not sure he would listen to me. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "And even if I summoned him and he responded, I’m not sure he would listen to me."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For he attacks me with a storm and repeatedly wounds me without cause. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For he attacks me with a storm and repeatedly wounds me without cause."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "He will not let me catch my breath, but fills me instead with bitter sorrows. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He will not let me catch my breath, but fills me instead with bitter sorrows."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "If it’s a question of strength, he’s the strong one. If it’s a matter of justice, who dares to summon him to court? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "If it’s a question of strength, he’s the strong one. If it’s a matter of justice, who dares to summon him to court?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Though I am innocent, my own mouth would pronounce me guilty. Though I am blameless, it would prove me wicked. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Though I am innocent, my own mouth would pronounce me guilty. Though I am blameless, it would prove me wicked."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“I am innocent, but it makes no difference to me— I despise my life. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“I am innocent, but it makes no difference to me— I despise my life."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Innocent or wicked, it is all the same to God. That’s why I say, ‘He destroys both the blameless and the wicked.’ "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Innocent or wicked, it is all the same to God. That’s why I say, ‘He destroys both the blameless and the wicked.’"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When a plague sweeps through, he laughs at the death of the innocent. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "When a plague sweeps through, he laughs at the death of the innocent."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The whole earth is in the hands of the wicked, and God blinds the eyes of the judges. If he’s not the one who does it, who is? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "The whole earth is in the hands of the wicked, and God blinds the eyes of the judges. If he’s not the one who does it, who is?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "The whole earth is in the hands of the wicked, and God blinds the eyes of the judges. If he’s not the one who does it, who is?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 25,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“My life passes more swiftly than a runner. It flees away without a glimpse of happiness. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 25,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“My life passes more swiftly than a runner. It flees away without a glimpse of happiness."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 25,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 26,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "It disappears like a swift papyrus boat, like an eagle swooping down on its prey. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 26,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "It disappears like a swift papyrus boat, like an eagle swooping down on its prey."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 26,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "If I decided to forget my complaints, to put away my sad face and be cheerful, "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "If I decided to forget my complaints, to put away my sad face and be cheerful,"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 28,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "I would still dread all the pain, for I know you will not find me innocent, O God. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 28,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "I would still dread all the pain, for I know you will not find me innocent, O God."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 28,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 29,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Whatever happens, I will be found guilty. So what’s the use of trying? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 29,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Whatever happens, I will be found guilty. So what’s the use of trying?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 29,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 30,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Even if I were to wash myself with soap and clean my hands with lye, "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 30,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Even if I were to wash myself with soap and clean my hands with lye,"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 30,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 31,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "you would plunge me into a muddy ditch, and my own filthy clothing would hate me. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 31,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "you would plunge me into a muddy ditch, and my own filthy clothing would hate me."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 31,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 32,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“God is not a mortal like me, so I cannot argue with him or take him to trial. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 32,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“God is not a mortal like me, so I cannot argue with him or take him to trial."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 32,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "If only there were a mediator between us, someone who could bring us together. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "If only there were a mediator between us, someone who could bring us together."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 34,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The mediator could make God stop beating me, and I would no longer live in terror of his punishment. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 34,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "The mediator could make God stop beating me, and I would no longer live in terror of his punishment."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 34,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 35,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Then I could speak to him without fear, but I cannot do that in my own strength. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 35,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Then I could speak to him without fear, but I cannot do that in my own strength."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}